               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17551204-3-off13-c37" targOrder="Y" targets="t17551204-3-defend41 t17551204-3-off13 t17551204-3-verdict15"></join>
         
               <p>3. (M) 
               
                  <persName id="t17551204-3-defend41" type="defendantName">
                     Joseph 
                     Stevens 
                  <interp inst="t17551204-3-defend41" type="surname" value="Stevens"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17551204-3-defend41" type="given" value="Joseph"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17551204-3-defend41" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17551204-3-off13" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17551204-3-off13" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17551204-3-off13" type="offenceSubcategory" value="shoplifting"></interp>
               stealing seven silk handkerchiefs, value 10 s. the goods of 
                     
                        <persName id="t17551204-3-victim43" type="victimName">
                           Samuel 
                           West 
                        <interp inst="t17551204-3-victim43" type="surname" value="West"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17551204-3-victim43" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17551204-3-victim43" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17551204-3-off13 t17551204-3-victim43"></join>
                     </persName>
                      
                  , privately in the shop
            </rs>, <rs id="t17551204-3-cd14" type="crimeDate">September 24</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17551204-3-off13 t17551204-3-cd14"></join>.* </p> 
               <p>Elizabeth West. On the 24th of September the prisoner came into our shop to buy some handkerchiefs. I shew'd him some; he did not like them; I shew'd him some others; he snatch'd some of them off the counter and ran away with them. I call'd stop thief and he was taken within a few yards of my shop, and brought back.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17551204-3-person44">
                  Thomas 
                  Young 
               <interp inst="t17551204-3-person44" type="surname" value="Young"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17551204-3-person44" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17551204-3-person44" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner came into my master's shop to buy some handkerchiefs; my mistress shew'd him some, he did not like them; she shew'd him some more, he took some up and said he'd have them for nothing; he ran out, I followed him, and had hold of his coat, when my master came and took him, and brought him back.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I was coming home from work about 8 o'clock, and there was a mob. I went to see what was the matter; there came a dog and laid hold on me; then a man came and said you are the lad that stole the handkerchiefs.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17551204-3-verdict15" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17551204-3-verdict15" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17551204-3-verdict15" type="verdictSubcategory" value="theftunder1s"></interp>
               Guilty 10 d.
            </rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17551204-3-punish16" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17551204-3-punish16" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17551204-3-defend41 t17551204-3-punish16"></join>
               
                     <note>[Transportation. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
